    "This pipeline is detailed in Newman et al. (2024).",
    "At a high level, the inputs are the query to Scholar QA, the section title, and the abstracts of all papers cited in the section.",
    "An LLM first produces a set of common aspects (columns) to compare papers (rows).",
    "Each cell (paper-aspect pair) is filled with a value using the full-text of the paper.",
    "Finally, as not all aspects are applicable to every paper (e.g., one paper might not be about a dataset), we filter out columns and rows with a high proportion of missing values."
